flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: New or updated production/telemetry/quality data indicating a potential constraint, disruption, or quality hold (e.g., unexpected equipment degradation, supply shortfall, or QC failure) ingested into the platform.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Ingest new telemetry, schedule, inventory and quality feeds from SAP, OT and Quality systems.]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: STREAMS - Normalize, validate and enrich raw feeds into subject area tables and compute derived downtime risk and impact metrics.]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Cortex RCA Service - Perform constraint detection and root-cause scoring; generate candidate recovery and sequencing scenarios with estimated costs and OTIF impact.]
  N3 --> N4{PB: Process Builder - Orchestrate rule-based evaluation and scenario simulation, selecting recommended action (stop, continue with adjust, partial hold) and whether to auto-execute or require CWB approval.}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[PB: Remote Functions - Execute approved action: writeback start/stop or reschedule to SAP S/4HANA and trigger operator instructions; isolate affected lots for QC if needed.]
  N5 --> N6[PB: CWB Lifecycle - Surface recommendations, exceptions and actions to operations for review; route unresolved or safety/quality-critical items via CWB for human approval.]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced COGS through improved line sequencing and reduced downtime, minimized waste from targeted holds, and maintained OTIF and availability via faster, coordinated recovery actions.]
  N4 -->|Detected condition violates safety or...| B1[Immediately stop affected line(s), escalate to operator/engineering, create high-priority CWB and block auto-execution.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Line stopped to preserve safety/quality; manual investigate-and-release workflow initiated; no automatic writeback until clearance.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Minor equipment anomaly with low down...| B2[Continue production with adjusted sequencing and increased monitoring; schedule maintenance during next planned downtime.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Throughput preserved, minimal disruption, and maintenance deferred to lower-cost window.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Supply disruption affecting specific ...| B3[Auto-reschedule remaining orders, sequence unaffected SKUs first, and trigger expedited procurement for missing components.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Minimized line idle time, reduced waste, and preserved customer commitments via alternate sequencing.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]